      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "7e0efa0f28b3401f75308b4d297639f6c2790873",
            "subject": "LU-13344 sec: remove time_t usage"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "James Simmons",
          "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
          "date": "2020-03-17 11:31:08.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2020-03-31 07:01:25.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-13344 servers: change request timeouts to s32",
        "message": "LU-13344 servers: change request timeouts to s32\n\nIn the latest kernels time_t has been removed since time_t has\nbeen a 64 bit value just like time64_t so no need for it anymore.\nThe field sf_run_time is stored on local media and its expected\nto be 32 bit in size so change it to s32 explictly. The fields\nthe MDT coordinator that are currently time_t are a simple change\nto s32 since they represent a time period and not a time stamp.\nLastly just update a comment in llog_swab.c since time_t will no\nlonger exist but we want to point out time in the llog is 32 bits\nin size.\n\nChange-Id: I0849fc9798c191d1fed77f7bba1357a209924418\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <jsimmons@infradead.org>\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/37950\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Shaun Tancheff <shaun.tancheff@hpe.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
  "requirements": [],
  "submit_records": []
